verse:
4 Hear the word of the Lord, you Israelites, because the Lord has a charge to bring against you who live in the land:
“There is no faithfulness, no love, no acknowledgment of God in the land. 2 There is only cursing,[a] lying and murder, stealing and adultery;
they break all bounds, and bloodshed follows bloodshed. 3 Because of this the land dries up, and all who live in it waste away;
the beasts of the field, the birds in the sky and the fish in the sea are swept away.
